<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: MUSIC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Shauna Snow, Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
'Mini-Season' for Bastille House: Paris' troubled Bastille Opera house is to 
raise the curtain on its first production next March but close its opera hall 
three months later for further technical fine-tuning. Directors of the new 
"People's Opera" commissioned by Socialist President Francois Mitterrand said 
Monday that the inaugural mini-season would feature two operas, concerts and 
recitals by some of the world's leading singers.Shauna Snow 
</P>
</TEXT>
